cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SY, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - This is the most likely category as the paper deals with the security of a self-synchronized stream cipher and introduces a new security model for such ciphers. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - Information theory is closely related to cryptography and the paper may involve concepts from information theory. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve computational complexity analysis of the proposed cipher or the security model. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may involve control systems theory as self-synchronization is a concept from control systems. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper may involve software engineering aspects of implementing the proposed cipher or the security model.
